🏏 Cricklytics: IPL Match Predictor
Cricklytics is a real-time web app that predicts the winning probability of an IPL team using live match inputs like target, score, overs, and wickets.
It combines data science with intuitive visualizations to give fans and analysts quick insights during a match.

🚀 Features
🧠 Win probability prediction (Logistic Regression)

🧹 Cleaned and preprocessed match-level IPL data

📊 EDA to explore trends in chases, scores, and win margins

🧪 Feature engineering:

Current Run Rate (CRR)

Required Run Rate (RRR)

Balls remaining, Wickets left, Target difference

📉 Visuals:

Horizontal win probability bar

Donut-style pie chart

Score vs Target bar chart

🧰 Tech Stack
Languages: Python

Libraries: Streamlit, Pandas, NumPy, scikit-learn, Matplotlib

Model: Logistic Regression (trained on past IPL match data)

📊 Data Workflow
Data Cleaning

Removed matches with missing or irrelevant data

Filtered matches with DL method or incomplete innings

EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis)

Examined impact of early wickets, high RRR, and venue bias

Identified useful features for model input

Feature Selection

CRR, RRR, Runs Left, Wickets Left, Remaining Balls

Teams, Host City

